			</td><td width="2%">&nbsp;</td><td width="44%"> Abstract
			<div style="text-align:justify;">
				<P>
					<B>Introduction</B>: The memory, individual and collective, is one of several topics studied in contemporary literature. Considering this, in this work, we sought to define the individual memory concepts, historical and collective and forgetfulness, and analyze how these concepts were built in the book "Before the birth of the world," Mia Couto (2009), and how the characters They relate them. For this, the theoretical foundation, told with theoretical addressing the themes of memory, as Rossi (2010), Olmi (2006) and especially Halbwachs (2003), which greatly contributes to their concerns about the construction of individual memory and collective. After analyzing the data, we clarified the concepts of quoted memories and forgetting. It was found also that the memory views, although they can be addressed separately, are interconnected as are constructed in the interaction. In the analyzed work, there is the attempt of the characters, private collective memory / history, to create a personal memory and thus be understood as subjects.					<B>Objectives</B>: The objective of this work plan is to analyze from the reading of "Before Sunrise the World" Mia Couto different memory concepts: personal, historical, collective, and of oblivion. Observe how the characters of the novel relate to these terms and how to build on their experiences, to forget and remember. We analyze this by observing the construction of identity and Mwanito Ntunzi, through its imaginary experience that indirectly trigger your memory and confront oblivion imposed by Silvestre.					<B>Methods</B>: The first step in the implementation of the project was the reading and BOOK REPORT key work to be analyzed Born -Before the world, Mia Couto. During August and September, was initiated to a second reading of the novel, but more attentive to the author of the particularities as well as the observation of a fundamental aspect of research: the representation of memory and the esqueciemento at work
The methodology used in this study was focused on indirect documentary research, which hosts the documentary research and literature. Thus, as of October, they followed up several theoretical readings on the issues involving different memory designs, whose scope was found mainly in Maurice Halwachs author of reference - Collective Memory (2003). The author proposed to contribute to the studies of the social sciences, the concept of collective memory, and defines social frameworks that make up this memory. In addition, of course, includes the study of individual and historical memory, as even being differentiated concepts do not cease to be interconnected. Through the investigation of these different memory concepts (personal, historical, collective) could be seen that the size of the memory certainly exceeds the individual level, this because the memories of an individual are not only their memory and can never be isolated from social enviroment.					<B>Results</B>: 					<B>Conclusion</B>: 				</P>
